  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Maria Weston Chapman reflects on people who want to &quot;feel the comfort of being a trampled minority after the time has gone by, and they are the party in power.&quot; She describes the effect of the current state of apprehension among the circle. Maria W. Chapman&apos;s own house was watched because of the cries heard, &quot;To Mrs. Chapman&apos;s!&quot; She tells of &quot;run-away rings&quot; at her door [people who run away after ringing her door]. In one case, the ringer later turned out to have been &quot;Willie Garrison,&quot; sent to fetch Mrs. Maria Chapman to Ann Terry Greene [Phillips]&apos;s house, who did not feel safe.</subfield>
